{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015wHyASQrw8aYz6h7YXxG68","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 12.3: Driver Health Check at Workflow Start\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want all referenced drivers health-checked before any task executes,\n11\tso that I get immediate feedback if a CLI is missing or unauthenticated instead of discovering it mid-workflow.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a workflow YAML referencing drivers `claude-code` and `codex`\n16\t   **When** `executeWorkflow()` is called\n17\t   **Then** the engine calls `healthCheck()` on every unique driver referenced in the workflow before executing any task\n18\t   **And** drivers are deduplicated (if three tasks use `claude-code`, `healthCheck()` is called once)\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** all drivers pass their health checks (all return `available: true`)\n22\t   **When** the health check phase completes\n23\t   **Then** the workflow proceeds to task execution normally\n24\t   **And** no error is logged or thrown\n25\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t3. **Given** one or more drivers fail their health check (return `available: false`)\n28\t   **When** the health check phase completes\n29\t   **Then** the engine aborts with a clear error listing ALL failing drivers and their error messages\n30\t   **And** the error message includes the driver name and the `error` field from `DriverHealth` for each failing driver\n31\t   **And** no tasks have been dispatched\n32\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n33\t\n34\t4. **Given** a workflow where all tasks use the default driver (`claude-code`, no explicit `driver` field)\n35\t   **When** `executeWorkflow()` is called\n36\t   **Then** only the `claude-code` driver's `healthCheck()` is called (one call total)\n37\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n38\t\n39\t5. **Given** the health check phase starts\n40\t   **When** all driver health checks are invoked\n41\t   **Then** all health checks run concurrently via `Promise.all()` (not sequentially)\n42\t   **And** the total health check phase completes within 5 seconds (NFR6 — enforced by a `Promise.race` with a 5-second timeout)\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t6. **Given** the health check phase exceeds the 5-second timeout (NFR6)\n46\t   **When** `Promise.race` resolves with the timeout\n47\t   **Then** the engine aborts with a clear error message indicating which drivers did not respond in time\n48\t   **And** no tasks have been dispatched\n49\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n50\t\n51\t7. **Given** a workflow state with `phase: 'completed'` (already finished)\n52\t   **When** `executeWorkflow()` is called\n53\t   **Then** the existing early-exit path returns immediately without calling any health checks\n54\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n55\t\n56\t8. **Given** driver registration occurs before `executeWorkflow()`\n57\t   **When** the engine collects unique driver names from the workflow\n58\t   **Then** it iterates `config.workflow.tasks`, reads each task's `driver` field (defaulting to `'claude-code'`), deduplicates, and calls `getDriver(name)` to resolve each to a registered `AgentDriver` before calling `healthCheck()`\n59\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n60\t\n61\t9. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n62\t   **When** the build completes\n63\t   **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n64\t   **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n65\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n66\t\n67\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n68\t\n69\t- [x] Task 1: Implement `checkDriverHealth()` function in `workflow-engine.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #5, #6, #8)\n70\t  - [x] Add a new exported async function `checkDriverHealth(workflow: ResolvedWorkflow): Promise<void>`\n71\t  - [x] Collect unique driver names from `workflow.tasks` — `task.driver ?? 'claude-code'` for each task\n72\t  - [x] Deduplicate driver names into a `Set<string>`\n73\t  - [x] For each unique driver name, call `getDriver(name)` to resolve the `AgentDriver`\n74\t  - [x] Run all `driver.healthCheck()` concurrently via `Promise.all()`\n75\t  - [x] Wrap with `Promise.race([healthChecks, timeout(5000)])` for NFR6 compliance\n76\t  - [x] If timeout fires, throw an error listing drivers that did not respond\n77\t  - [x] After all checks complete, collect failures (where `available === false`)\n78\t  - [x] If any failures, throw an error listing all failing driver names and their `error` messages\n79\t  - [x] If all pass, return void (success)\n80\t\n81\t- [x] Task 2: Integrate `checkDriverHealth()` into `executeWorkflow()` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #7)\n82\t  - [x] Add the health check call after workflow state initialization but BEFORE the work-items loading / flow-step iteration\n83\t  - [x] Place it after the early exit for `phase === 'completed'` (so completed workflows skip health checks)\n84\t  - [x] Wrap in try/catch — on failure, set `phase: 'failed'`, push error to `errors[]`, return early with `success: false`\n85\t\n86\t- [x] Task 3: Write unit tests for `checkDriverHealth()` (AC: #1-#9)\n87\t  - [x] Test: single driver, health check passes — no error thrown\n88\t  - [x] Test: multiple unique drivers, all pass — no error thrown\n89\t  - [x] Test: deduplicated drivers — `healthCheck()` called once per unique driver\n90\t  - [x] Test: one driver fails — error thrown listing the failing driver and its error message\n91\t  - [x] Test: multiple drivers fail — error lists ALL failing drivers, not just the first\n92\t  - [x] Test: default driver (`claude-code`) used when task has no `driver` field\n93\t  - [x] Test: timeout — if health check hangs, error thrown after 5 seconds\n94\t  - [x] Test: completed workflow skips health checks entirely\n95\t\n96\t- [x] Task 4: Verify build and tests (AC: #9)\n97\t  - [x] Run `npm run build` — zero TypeScript errors\n98\t  - [x] Run `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, no regressions\n99\t\n100\t## Dev Notes\n101\t\n102\t### Architecture Compliance\n103\t\n104\tThis story implements Epic 3, Story 3.3 (mapped to sprint Epic 12, Story 12-3) \"Driver Health Check at Workflow Start\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers:\n105\t- **NFR6:** Driver health check (all drivers in workflow) must complete within 5 seconds at workflow start.\n106\t- **FR2/FR3 (enforcement):** The health check uses each driver's existing `healthCheck()` method (implemented in stories 10-3, 12-1, 12-2). This story wires the checks into the workflow engine pre-flight.\n107\t\n108\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n109\t- **Decision 1 (Driver Interface):** `healthCheck()` is already part of `AgentDriver`. This story consumes it — no interface changes.\n110\t- **Flow from architecture-multi-framework.md:** `driver-factory → get driver by name → driver.healthCheck()` — this story implements exactly this call path at workflow start.\n111\t\n112\t### Implementation Strategy\n113\t\n114\tThe change is localized to `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`:\n115\t\n116\t1. **New function `checkDriverHealth()`** — pure function that takes a `ResolvedWorkflow`, extracts unique drivers, runs health checks concurrently with a 5-second timeout. Throws on failure. This is testable in isolation.\n117\t\n118\t2. **Integration into `executeWorkflow()`** — a single call to `checkDriverHealth()` inserted between state initialization and work-item loading. The existing early-exit for `phase === 'completed'` remains above it.\n119\t\n120\t### Where to Insert in `executeWorkflow()`\n121\t\n122\tCurrent flow (line numbers approximate):\n123\t```\n124\t738: export async function executeWorkflow(config)\n125\t745:   let state = readWorkflowState(...)\n126\t748:   if (state.phase === 'completed') return;  // <-- keep this ABOVE health check\n127\t759:   state = { ...state, phase: 'executing', ... }\n128\t765:   writeWorkflowState(state, projectDir)\n129\t767:   // 2. Load work items                      // <-- INSERT health check BEFORE this\n130\t768:   const workItems = loadWorkItems(...)\n131\t```\n132\t\n133\tInsert the health check call between line 765 (write state) and line 767 (load work items). This ensures:\n134\t- Completed workflows skip health checks (early exit on line 748)\n135\t- State is already written as `executing` before health checks run\n136\t- If health checks fail, no work items are loaded and no tasks dispatched\n137\t\n138\t### Key API Surface\n139\t\n140\t```typescript\n141\t// New export from workflow-engine.ts\n142\texport async function checkDriverHealth(workflow: ResolvedWorkflow): Promise<void>;\n143\t```\n144\t\n145\tInternally uses:\n146\t- `getDriver(name)` from `./agents/drivers/factory.js` (already imported)\n147\t- `driver.healthCheck()` from `AgentDriver` interface\n148\t- `ResolvedWorkflow` from `./workflow-parser.js` (already imported)\n149\t\n150\t### What NOT to Do\n151\t\n152\t- Do NOT modify `factory.ts` — only consume `getDriver()`.\n153\t- Do NOT modify any driver files (`claude-code.ts`, `codex.ts`, `opencode.ts`) — health check logic is already implemented.\n154\t- Do NOT modify `types.ts` — `DriverHealth` and `AgentDriver` already exist.\n155\t- Do NOT modify `workflow-parser.ts` — `ResolvedTask.driver` already exists.\n156\t- Do NOT run health checks sequentially — use `Promise.all()` for concurrency.\n157\t- Do NOT swallow health check errors — the whole point is to surface them clearly.\n158\t- Do NOT add new dependencies — only use existing imports.\n159\t- Do NOT change the `EngineConfig` interface — the workflow is already available on `config.workflow`.\n160\t\n161\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n162\t\n163\tFrom story 12-2 (OpenCode Driver Implementation):\n164\t- 64 new tests added, 4478 total passing across 166 test files.\n165\t- `healthCheck()` on `OpenCodeDriver` checks `which opencode`, version, and optional auth. Returns `DriverHealth`.\n166\t- All three CLI drivers (`claude-code`, `codex`, `opencode`) have `healthCheck()` implemented identically in structure.\n167\t\n168\tFrom story 12-1 (Codex Driver Implementation):\n169\t- `healthCheck()` on `CodexDriver` checks `which codex`, `codex --version`, and auth. Same `DriverHealth` return type.\n170\t- `IGNORE:` comments required on catch blocks for linter compliance.\n171\t\n172\tFrom story 10-5 (Workflow Engine Driver Integration):\n173\t- `getDriver()` is already imported and used in `workflow-engine.ts` (line 7).\n174\t- Driver resolution happens per-task at dispatch time (line 293-294). This story adds pre-flight validation at workflow start.\n175\t\n176\t### Git Intelligence\n177\t\n178\tRecent commits (all in current sprint):\n179\t- `1ed6db3` — story 12-2: OpenCode Driver Implementation\n180\t- `6edd1df` — story 12-1: Codex Driver Implementation\n181\t- `44c0b70` — story 11-2: workflow referential integrity validation\n182\t- `a4bf7e6` — story 11-1: workflow schema extension\n183\t- `f128064` — story 10-5: workflow engine driver integration\n184\t\n185\t### Testing Patterns\n186\t\n187\tFollow the existing `workflow-engine.test.ts` patterns:\n188\t- Mock `getDriver()` via `vi.mock('./agents/drivers/factory.js', ...)`\n189\t- Create mock `AgentDriver` objects with `healthCheck` returning `Promise<DriverHealth>`\n190\t- Use `vi.fn()` for health check methods to verify call counts (deduplication)\n191\t- Test timeout by having a mock `healthCheck` that never resolves (use `new Promise(() => {})`)\n192\t- Verify error messages contain failing driver names and error strings\n193\t\n194\t### Project Structure Notes\n195\t\n196\tFiles to MODIFY:\n197\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — Add `checkDriverHealth()` function and integrate into `executeWorkflow()`\n198\t\n199\tFiles to possibly MODIFY:\n200\t- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — Add tests for health check behavior (or create a focused test file if the existing one is large)\n201\t\n202\tFiles NOT to modify:\n203\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts` — consume only\n204\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts` — already has healthCheck\n205\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/codex.ts` — already has healthCheck\n206\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/opencode.ts` — already has healthCheck\n207\t- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — DriverHealth, AgentDriver already exist\n208\t- `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — ResolvedTask.driver already exists\n209\t\n210\t### References\n211\t\n212\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 3.3: Driver Health Check at Workflow Start]\n213\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — driver-factory → get driver by name → driver.healthCheck()]\n214\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md — NFR6: Driver health check must complete within 5 seconds]\n215\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md — Driver health check at startup]\n216\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — executeWorkflow() function, lines 738+]\n217\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — DriverHealth, AgentDriver interfaces]\n218\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts — getDriver()]\n219\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-2-opencode-driver-implementation.md — previous story context]\n220\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-1-codex-driver-implementation.md — codex driver context]\n221\t\n222\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n223\t## Verification Requirements\n224\t\n225\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start-proof.md)\n226\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n227\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n228\t\n229\t## Documentation Requirements\n230\t\n231\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n232\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start.md\n233\t\n234\t## Testing Requirements\n235\t\n236\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n237\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n238\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n239\t\n240\t## Dev Agent Record\n241\t\n242\t### Agent Model Used\n243\t\n244\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n245\t\n246\t### Debug Log References\n247\t\n248\tNone.\n249\t\n250\t### Completion Notes List\n251\t\n252\t- Implemented `checkDriverHealth()` in `workflow-engine.ts` with concurrent health checks and 5s timeout\n253\t- Integrated into `executeWorkflow()` after state initialization, before work item loading\n254\t- Added optional `timeoutMs` parameter for testability (defaults to 5000ms)\n255\t- Created dedicated test file `driver-health-check.test.ts` with 10 tests covering all ACs\n256\t- Updated existing test mock to return healthy `DriverHealth` from `healthCheck()`\n257\t- Updated one existing test assertion (`mockGetDriver` call count) to account for health check call\n258\t- Build: 0 TypeScript errors. Tests: 4488 passed, 0 failed, 167 test files.\n259\t\n260\t### File List\n261\t\n262\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — Added `checkDriverHealth()` function and integration into `executeWorkflow()`\n263\t- `src/lib/__tests__/driver-health-check.test.ts` — New test file with 10 tests for health check behavior\n264\t- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — Updated mock and assertion for health check compatibility\n265\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NyfUq8vxhxtYfk2LGppqTU","session_id":"be33ba5d-0e81-49c4-ae53-e69ac56cd1fb","uuid":"4e77b675-4ed3-45ed-bcd4-02f94cba2f52","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:04:18.752Z"}
