{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NyfUq8vxhxtYfk2LGppqTU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization.md`.\n\n**What was done:**\n- Auto-discovered story 13-1 (`output-contract-schema-serialization`) as the next backlog item from `sprint-status.yaml`\n- Mapped it to Epic 4, Story 4.1 from `epics-multi-framework.md` and architecture Decision 3 from `architecture-multi-framework.md`\n- Created a full story file with 10 acceptance criteria, 5 task groups with subtasks, dev notes, architecture compliance, and implementation strategy\n- All 10 ACs tagged `<!-- verification: test-provable -->` — every AC is verifiable via build + unit tests without running the app or needing a Docker stack\n- Followed the exact format of the previous story (12-3) including Dev Notes structure, What NOT to Do section, and References\n\n**Key decisions:**\n- The `OutputContract` type already exists in `types.ts` — no interface changes needed\n- Module follows the existing `writeFileSync` + `renameSync` atomic write pattern from `sprint/state.ts`\n- Workflow engine integration is explicitly deferred to story 13-3 (Cross-Framework Workflow Execution)\n- Sync I/O chosen over async to match existing codebase conventions\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Ambiguity: contract directory parameter vs hardcoded path.** The architecture says `.codeharness/contracts/` but passing `contractDir` as a parameter is more testable and follows the existing pattern where the project dir is resolved at the engine level. Chose parameterized API.\n- **Ambiguity: error handling pattern.** The codebase uses both `Result<T>` (sprint module) and thrown errors (workflow engine). Chose thrown errors since the output contract module is consumed by the workflow engine, which already uses try/catch.\n- **Risk: None significant.** All ACs are test-provable. The module is self-contained with no external dependencies.\n- **Observation:** The `output_contract` field already exists in workflow schema and parser (as a task-level schema config), but it serves a different purpose than the runtime contract files this story creates. The naming overlap could confuse implementers — the Dev Notes \"What NOT to Do\" section explicitly calls this out.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 5, Glob: 5, Grep: 3, Write: 1, Edit: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `git log --oneline` (~5 lines), `wc -l` (~1 line), `ls` (~7 lines)\n- Files read: 6 unique, 7 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8b02430be33a7c97 (use SendMessage with to: 'a8b02430be33a7c97' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 55493\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 154329</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be33ba5d-0e81-49c4-ae53-e69ac56cd1fb","uuid":"fbee426f-0949-4854-a820-b00bb6d481f8","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:06:26.231Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /create-story for story 13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append a verification tier tag using this decision tree:\n\n**Tier Decision Tree (append one `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag per AC):**\n- `test-provable` — AC can be verified by building the project and running tests/linters/grep. No running app needed. Examples: 'function X exists', 'type Y is exported', 'test Z passes', 'file has <300 lines'.\n- `runtime-provable` — AC requires running the app locally and checking its behavior (CLI output, HTTP response, process lifecycle). No Docker stack needed. Examples: 'CLI prints usage when invoked with --help', 'server responds 200 on /health', 'process exits 0 on valid input'.\n- `environment-provable` — AC requires a full environment (Docker stack, database, observability, multi-service interaction). Examples: 'logs appear in VictoriaLogs', 'metrics are emitted to VictoriaMetrics', 'container communicates with service X'.\n- `escalate` — AC genuinely cannot be automated (requires physical hardware, paid external service, human visual judgment). This is rare. Examples: 'UI looks correct on mobile', 'payment processes successfully in production'.\n\nDefault to `test-provable` when unsure. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (errors, ambiguities in epic definition, missing context)\n- Workarounds applied (anything you did that felt hacky or suboptimal)\n- Risks identified (ACs that seem untestable, unclear requirements, missing dependencies)\n- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy about this story)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls","agentId":"a8b02430be33a7c97","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization.md`.\n\n**What was done:**\n- Auto-discovered story 13-1 (`output-contract-schema-serialization`) as the next backlog item from `sprint-status.yaml`\n- Mapped it to Epic 4, Story 4.1 from `epics-multi-framework.md` and architecture Decision 3 from `architecture-multi