{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CvXemKtrm7egBFmYX1dctA","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be33ba5d-0e81-49c4-ae53-e69ac56cd1fb","uuid":"142db4cc-33d9-454a-8d42-9e0f811c0f85","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:10:27.597Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"Token Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 5, Glob: 5, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 6 unique files. No redundancy.","newString":"Token Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 5, Glob: 5, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 6 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization — dev-story (2026-04-03T10:08)\n\nNo issues reported. 11/11 new tests pass, 4500 tests across 168 files, zero regressions.\n\nToken Report: 17 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 5, Edit: 5, Write: 3). 5 unique files, 6 total reads. One re-read for Edit mismatch.","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 9)\n\n### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — create-story (2026-04-03T09:20)\n\n- **Ambiguity: OpenCode CLI output format.** Architecture doc acknowledges must be \"reverse-engineered from real CLI output.\" Fixtures will be plausible guesses.\n- **Ambiguity: OpenCode auth check command.** Used `opencode auth status` as guess. Low risk — health check gracefully handles command failure.\n- **No project-context.md found** — workflow references it but none exists. No impact.\n- **Risk: classifyError duplication.** Both CodexDriver and OpenCodeDriver have identical implementations. Intentional per architecture.\n\nToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 7, Grep: 4, Glob: 2, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 10 unique files read. No redundancy.\n\n### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — dev-story (2026-04-03T09:25)\n\nNo issues reported. Build passes, 4478 tests pass across 166 test files, zero regressions.\n\nToken Report: 20 tool calls (Bash: 4, Read: 11, Edit: 3, Write: 6, Glob: 2, Skill: 1). 11 unique files, 12 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — code-review (2026-04-03T09:30)\n\n- **LOW: Dead fixture files.** test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/*.txt exist but tests use inline data. Dead artifacts.\n- **LOW: classifyError/parseLine duplication.** ~80 identical lines between codex.ts and opencode.ts. Intentional per architecture.\n- **LOW: console.debug for unparseable lines.** No structured logger. Shared pattern across drivers.\n- No HIGH or MEDIUM issues. 96.78% coverage. All 169 files above 80% floor.\n\nToken Report: 12 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 7, Edit: 1, Grep: 1, Glob: 3, Skill: 1). 8 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — verify (2026-04-03T09:35)\n\n- **Stale AGENTS.md precondition:** `codeharness verify` fails due to stale AGENTS.md files for src/lib/agents/drivers module. Pre-existing documentation debt, not story-related.\n- **Test count discrepancy:** Story changelog claims 64 tests, actual count is 69. Minor — 69 is current state.\n- **Branch coverage 96.03%:** 4 uncovered branches at lines 149, 198, 306-307 (edge cases in parseLine result handling and error catch block).\n- ALL_PASS: 11/11 ACs verified with evidence.\n\nToken Report: 11 tool calls (Bash: 7, Read: 3, Write: 1). 3 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start — create-story (2026-04-03T09:39)\n\n- **Multiple epics files with different 12-3 definitions.** Correct source is epics-multi-framework.md based on sprint-status context.\n- **Risk: 5-second timeout NFR6** requires careful mock design with fake timers to avoid real waits in tests.\n- All 9 ACs tagged test-provable. Small, well-scoped story (~100-150 lines prod, ~150-200 lines tests).\n\nToken Report: 21 tool calls (Bash: 2, Read: 8, Grep: 7, Write: 1, Glob: 3, Skill: 1). 10 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start — dev-story (2026-04-03T09:45)\n\n- **Workaround: optional timeoutMs parameter** added to `checkDriverHealth()` for testability (fake timers caused unhandled rejection warnings). Clean solution, not in original spec.\n- **Existing test impact:** Updated `healthCheck` mock in workflow-engine.test.ts to return valid `DriverHealth` object. Updated `mockGetDriver` call count assertion (+1 for health check).\n- **Code quality concern:** `setTimeout` in `checkDriverHealth` not cleared after `Promise.all` resolves — standard Promise.race behavior but could use cleanup.\n- Build passes (0 errors), 4488 tests pass across 167 files, zero regressions.\n\nToken Report: 19 tool calls (Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 7, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Glob: 1). 6 unique files, 10 total reads. workflow-engine.test.ts read 4x, workflow-engine.ts read 3x. One redundant npm run build call.\n\n### 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start — code-review (2026-04-03T09:51)\n\n- **HIGH: Timer leak fixed.** `setTimeout` never cleared on success path in `checkDriverHealth()`. Added `clearTimeout`.\n- **MEDIUM: Timeout error inaccuracy fixed.** Was reporting ALL drivers instead of only non-responding ones (AC #6 violation).\n- **MEDIUM: Double mock invocation fixed.** Test called `checkDriverHealth` twice per assertion.\n- **MEDIUM: Missing test added.** \"timeout error reports only drivers that did not respond\".\n- **LOW (not fixed): `HealthResult` type** defined inline in function body rather than module scope. Cosmetic.\n- Coverage: 96.79% overall, all 169 files above 80% floor.\n\nToken Report: 21 tool calls (Bash: 10, Read: 6, Edit: 4, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 8 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start — verify (2026-04-03T09:55)\n\n- **Proof format mismatch:** Verifier subagent generated `### AC N:` headers but parser expects `## AC N:`. Also needed `bash`/`output` code block pairs. Manually rewrote proof document.\n- **Stale AGENTS.md files:** Fixed src/lib/agents/AGENTS.md, src/lib/AGENTS.md, created src/lib/agents/drivers/AGENTS.md. Pre-existing debt from stories 12-1/12-2.\n- **Pre-existing lint error:** `require-yield` at workflow-engine.test.ts:154. Not from this story.\n- ALL_PASS: 9/9 ACs verified. `codeharness verify` passes.\n\nToken Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 2, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 3 unique files. npm run test:unit run twice (verbose + summary).\n\n### 13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization — create-story (2026-04-03T10:04)\n\n- **Ambiguity: contract directory parameter vs hardcoded path.** Architecture says `.codeharness/contracts/` but parameterized API chosen for testability.\n- **Ambiguity: error handling pattern.** Codebase uses both `Result<T>` and thrown errors. Chose thrown errors to match workflow engine convention.\n- **Observation:** `output_contract` field already exists in workflow schema for a different purpose (task-level schema config vs runtime contract files). Naming overlap noted in Dev Notes.\n\nToken Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 5, Glob: 5, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 6 unique files. No redundancy.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":77,"oldLines":3,"newStart":77,"newLines":9,"lines":[" - **Observation:** `output_contract` field already exists in workflow schema for a different purpose (task-level schema config vs runtime contract files). Naming overlap noted in Dev Notes."," "," Token Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 5, Glob: 5, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 6 unique files. No redundancy.","+","+### 13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization — dev-story (2026-04-03T10:08)","+","+No issues reported. 11/11 new tests pass, 4500 tests across 168 files, zero regressions.","+","+Token Report: 17 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 5, Edit: 5, Write: 3). 5 unique files, 6 total reads. One re-read for Edit mismatch."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
