{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UxRJmFjB9LC4GbkvGNEx4U","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 13.1: Output Contract Schema & Serialization\n2\t\n3\tStatus: review\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want output contracts serialized as JSON files with atomic writes,\n11\tso that task results survive crashes and can be read by the next task in a cross-framework workflow.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a new `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` module\n16\t   **When** the module is imported\n17\t   **Then** it exports `writeOutputContract(contract: OutputContract, contractDir: string): void` that writes a contract to disk\n18\t   **And** it exports `readOutputContract(taskName: string, storyId: string, contractDir: string): OutputContract | null` that reads a contract from disk\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** a valid `OutputContract` object and a target directory\n22\t   **When** `writeOutputContract()` is called\n23\t   **Then** the contract is written to `{contractDir}/{taskName}-{storyId}.json`\n24\t   **And** the write is atomic: first written to a `.tmp` file, then renamed to the final path\n25\t   **And** the `.tmp` file does not remain on disk after a successful write\n26\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n27\t\n28\t3. **Given** a contract file exists at `{contractDir}/{taskName}-{storyId}.json`\n29\t   **When** `readOutputContract(taskName, storyId, contractDir)` is called\n30\t   **Then** the function returns the deserialized `OutputContract` object with all fields intact\n31\t   **And** the returned object matches the `OutputContract` interface from `types.ts`\n32\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n33\t\n34\t4. **Given** no contract file exists for the given `taskName` and `storyId`\n35\t   **When** `readOutputContract()` is called\n36\t   **Then** it returns `null` (not an error)\n37\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n38\t\n39\t5. **Given** a contract where optional fields (`testResults`, `cost_usd`) are `null`\n40\t   **When** `writeOutputContract()` is called and then `readOutputContract()` reads it back\n41\t   **Then** the `null` values are preserved (not omitted, not converted to `0` or `undefined`)\n42\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n43\t\n44\t6. **Given** a new `src/schemas/output-contract.schema.json` JSON Schema file\n45\t   **When** validated against the `OutputContract` interface in `types.ts`\n46\t   **Then** the schema defines all required fields: `version`, `taskName`, `storyId`, `driver`, `model`, `timestamp`, `cost_usd`, `duration_ms`, `changedFiles`, `testResults`, `output`, `acceptanceCriteria`\n47\t   **And** `cost_usd` allows `number | null`\n48\t   **And** `testResults` allows object | null\n49\t   **And** `changedFiles` is an array of strings\n50\t   **And** `acceptanceCriteria` is an array of objects with `id`, `description`, `status` fields\n51\t   **And** `version` is a number (fixed at `1` for initial release)\n52\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n53\t\n54\t7. **Given** `writeOutputContract()` is called and the target directory does not exist\n55\t   **When** the function executes\n56\t   **Then** it creates the directory recursively (like `mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true })`) before writing\n57\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n58\t\n59\t8. **Given** a contract of approximately 1MB in size\n60\t   **When** `writeOutputContract()` serializes it and `readOutputContract()` deserializes it\n61\t   **Then** the round-trip completes within 1 second (NFR4)\n62\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n63\t\n64\t9. **Given** `writeOutputContract()` fails mid-write (e.g., disk error during temp file write)\n65\t   **When** the error occurs\n66\t   **Then** the function throws an error with a descriptive message including the file path\n67\t   **And** no partial final file is left on disk (the `.tmp` file may remain, but the final path is not corrupted)\n68\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n69\t\n70\t10. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n71\t    **When** the build completes\n72\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n73\t    **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n74\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n75\t\n76\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n77\t\n78\t- [x] Task 1: Create `src/schemas/output-contract.schema.json` (AC: #6)\n79\t  - [x] Define JSON Schema with `$schema`, `title`, `type: object`, and `required` array listing all 12 fields\n80\t  - [x] Define `version` as `{ type: \"number\" }`\n81\t  - [x] Define `taskName`, `storyId`, `driver`, `model`, `timestamp`, `output` as `{ type: \"string\" }`\n82\t  - [x] Define `cost_usd` as `{ type: [\"number\", \"null\"] }`\n83\t  - [x] Define `duration_ms` as `{ type: \"number\" }`\n84\t  - [x] Define `changedFiles` as `{ type: \"array\", items: { type: \"string\" } }`\n85\t  - [x] Define `testResults` as `{ oneOf: [{ type: \"null\" }, { type: \"object\", properties: { passed: number, failed: number, coverage: [\"number\", \"null\"] }, required: [...] }] }`\n86\t  - [x] Define `acceptanceCriteria` as `{ type: \"array\", items: { type: \"object\", properties: { id: string, description: string, status: string }, required: [...] } }`\n87\t\n88\t- [x] Task 2: Create `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` module (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5, #7, #9)\n89\t  - [x] Import `writeFileSync`, `readFileSync`, `renameSync`, `mkdirSync`, `existsSync` from `node:fs`\n90\t  - [x] Import `join`, `dirname` from `node:path`\n91\t  - [x] Import `OutputContract` type from `./types.js`\n92\t  - [x] Implement `contractFilePath(taskName: string, storyId: string, contractDir: string): string` helper that returns `join(contractDir, \\`\\${taskName}-\\${storyId}.json\\`)`\n93\t  - [x] Implement `writeOutputContract(contract: OutputContract, contractDir: string): void`\n94\t    - [x] Ensure directory exists: `mkdirSync(contractDir, { recursive: true })`\n95\t    - [x] Compute final path from `contractFilePath(contract.taskName, contract.storyId, contractDir)`\n96\t    - [x] Compute temp path: `finalPath + '.tmp'`\n97\t    - [x] `writeFileSync(tmpPath, JSON.stringify(contract, null, 2) + '\\n', 'utf-8')`\n98\t    - [x] `renameSync(tmpPath, finalPath)`\n99\t    - [x] Wrap in try/catch — on failure, throw with descriptive message including the file path\n100\t  - [x] Implement `readOutputContract(taskName: string, storyId: string, contractDir: string): OutputContract | null`\n101\t    - [x] Compute path from `contractFilePath(taskName, storyId, contractDir)`\n102\t    - [x] If file does not exist (`!existsSync(path)`), return `null`\n103\t    - [x] `readFileSync(path, 'utf-8')` → `JSON.parse()` → return as `OutputContract`\n104\t\n105\t- [x] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#10)\n106\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/agents/__tests__/output-contract.test.ts`\n107\t  - [x] Test: `writeOutputContract` creates file at correct path (`{taskName}-{storyId}.json`)\n108\t  - [x] Test: `writeOutputContract` uses atomic write (write to `.tmp`, then rename — verify no `.tmp` remains)\n109\t  - [x] Test: `readOutputContract` returns the deserialized contract with all fields intact\n110\t  - [x] Test: `readOutputContract` returns `null` when file does not exist\n111\t  - [x] Test: round-trip preserves `null` values for `cost_usd` and `testResults`\n112\t  - [x] Test: `writeOutputContract` creates directory recursively when it does not exist\n113\t  - [x] Test: `writeOutputContract` throws descriptive error on write failure\n114\t  - [x] Test: round-trip for a ~1MB contract completes within 1 second (NFR4 performance test)\n115\t  - [x] Test: JSON Schema in `output-contract.schema.json` validates a correct contract\n116\t  - [x] Test: JSON Schema rejects a contract missing required fields\n117\t\n118\t- [x] Task 4: Export from barrel file (AC: #1)\n119\t  - [x] Add `writeOutputContract` and `readOutputContract` exports to `src/lib/agents/index.ts`\n120\t\n121\t- [x] Task 5: Verify build and tests (AC: #10)\n122\t  - [x] Run `npm run build` — zero TypeScript errors\n123\t  - [x] Run `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, no regressions\n124\t\n125\t## Dev Notes\n126\t\n127\t### Architecture Compliance\n128\t\n129\tThis story implements Epic 4, Story 4.1 (mapped to sprint Epic 13, Story 13-1) \"Output Contract Schema & Serialization\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers:\n130\t- **FR17:** System can serialize a task's output contract to a structured JSON file after task completion\n131\t- **NFR4:** Output contract serialization/deserialization must complete within 1 second for contracts up to 1MB\n132\t- **NFR10:** Output contract JSON format must be stable across driver versions\n133\t- **NFR15:** Output contract files must survive engine crashes — written atomically\n134\t\n135\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n136\t- **Decision 3 (Output Contract Format):** JSON files in `.codeharness/contracts/{taskName}-{storyId}.json`. Written atomically (write to `.tmp`, then rename). Version field for format evolution.\n137\t- **Output Contract Population Pattern:** Drivers set `changedFiles`, `testResults`, `output`, `cost_usd`. Fields not available are `null`.\n138\t\n139\t### Implementation Strategy\n140\t\n141\tThis story creates a standalone module — no modifications to existing files (except the barrel `index.ts`). The workflow engine integration (calling `writeOutputContract` after task dispatch) belongs to story 13-3 (Cross-Framework Workflow Execution).\n142\t\n143\tThe module follows the same atomic write pattern used in `src/modules/sprint/state.ts`:\n144\t```typescript\n145\twriteFileSync(tmpPath, data, 'utf-8');\n146\trenameSync(tmpPath, finalPath);\n147\t```\n148\t\n149\t### What Already Exists\n150\t\n151\t- `OutputContract` interface — defined in `src/lib/agents/types.ts` (lines 67-80) with all required fields\n152\t- `TestResults` interface — defined in `src/lib/agents/types.ts` (lines 49-53)\n153\t- `ACStatus` interface — defined in `src/lib/agents/types.ts` (lines 58-62)\n154\t- `DispatchOpts.outputContract` — already accepts `OutputContract` for injection into next task\n155\t- The `.codeharness/contracts/` directory convention is defined in the architecture but does not yet exist at runtime\n156\t\n157\t### What NOT to Do\n158\t\n159\t- Do NOT modify `types.ts` — `OutputContract`, `TestResults`, `ACStatus` already exist and are correct.\n160\t- Do NOT modify `workflow-engine.ts` — engine integration is story 13-3.\n161\t- Do NOT modify `workflow-parser.ts` — the `output_contract` field on tasks is for schema-level config, not runtime contract files.\n162\t- Do NOT add schema validation at write time — the TypeScript type system is sufficient. Schema is for external tooling and documentation.\n163\t- Do NOT use async I/O — the existing codebase uses sync filesystem operations (`writeFileSync`, `renameSync`) for atomic writes. Follow the same pattern for consistency.\n164\t\n165\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n166\t\n167\tFrom story 12-3 (Driver Health Check at Workflow Start):\n168\t- 4488 tests passing across 167 test files.\n169\t- `getDriver()` and `healthCheck()` wired into `executeWorkflow()` pre-flight.\n170\t- All driver infrastructure (factory, claude-code, codex, opencode) is complete and tested.\n171\t\n172\tFrom the sprint/state.ts atomic write pattern:\n173\t- `writeFileSync` to `.tmp`, then `renameSync` to final path.\n174\t- Wrap in try/catch, return `Result<void>` pattern (but this module can throw instead — simpler for this use case).\n175\t\n176\t### Testing Patterns\n177\t\n178\tFollow existing agent test patterns in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/`:\n179\t- Use `mkdtempSync` for isolated temp directories per test\n180\t- Clean up temp dirs in `afterEach`\n181\t- For the 1MB performance test, generate a contract with a large `output` field (~1MB string)\n182\t- For atomic write verification, check that no `.tmp` file remains after `writeOutputContract`\n183\t- For error testing, use a read-only directory or non-existent deeply nested path\n184\t\n185\t### Project Structure Notes\n186\t\n187\tFiles to CREATE:\n188\t- `src/schemas/output-contract.schema.json` — JSON Schema for output contract format\n189\t- `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` — serialize/deserialize module\n190\t- `src/lib/agents/__tests__/output-contract.test.ts` — unit tests\n191\t\n192\tFiles to MODIFY:\n193\t- `src/lib/agents/index.ts` — add barrel exports for `writeOutputContract`, `readOutputContract`\n194\t\n195\tFiles NOT to modify:\n196\t- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — OutputContract already defined\n197\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — integration is story 13-3\n198\t- `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — output_contract field is separate concern\n199\t- Any driver files — drivers are not involved in this story\n200\t\n201\t### References\n202\t\n203\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 4.1: Output Contract Schema & Serialization]\n204\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Decision 3: Output Contract Format]\n205\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Output Contract Population Pattern]\n206\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — OutputContract, TestResults, ACStatus interfaces]\n207\t- [Source: src/modules/sprint/state.ts — writeStateAtomic() atomic write pattern]\n208\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/index.ts — barrel exports]\n209\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start.md — previous story context]\n210\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01YSacQvkrW7LZee36oBUg8s","session_id":"be33ba5d-0e81-49c4-ae53-e69ac56cd1fb","uuid":"316fc886-9ecc-4465-a422-ee7b777578ce","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:10:50.092Z"}
