{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YSacQvkrW7LZee36oBUg8s","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization\n**Story Status:** `verifying`\n**Issues Found:** 2 High, 4 Medium, 3 Low\n**Issues Fixed:** 2 High, 3 Medium (6 total)\n**Tests:** 4506 passed (168 files), 0 regressions, +6 new tests\n**Build:** Zero TypeScript errors\n**Coverage:** 96.79% overall (above 90% target), all 170 files above 80% per-file floor\n\n### Files modified:\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` — Added input validation (`assertSafeComponent`), path traversal protection, and error handling for `readOutputContract` JSON parse failures\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/__tests__/output-contract.test.ts` — Added 6 tests: path traversal rejection (2), empty input rejection (2), corrupted JSON handling (1), platform guard on chmod test (1)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization.md` — Status changed from `review` to `verifying`\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- **HIGH** — Path traversal vulnerability: `taskName` containing `../` could write files outside `contractDir`. Fixed with `assertSafeComponent` validation and resolved path containment check.\n- **HIGH** — No input validation: empty `taskName`/`storyId` strings produced nonsensical filenames like `-.json`. Fixed by rejecting empty/whitespace-only strings.\n- **MEDIUM** — `readOutputContract` had no error handling for corrupted JSON files. A `SyntaxError` from `JSON.parse` would propagate with no file context. Fixed with try/catch wrapping.\n- **MEDIUM** — Test for write failure used `chmodSync` without platform guard — would fail on Windows. Fixed with `it.skipIf(platform() === 'win32')`.\n- **MEDIUM** — Unused import `relative` from `node:path` introduced during fix. Cleaned up.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- Schema `additionalProperties: false` creates silent incompatibility if TypeScript interface gains new fields without schema update. No runtime schema validation at write time — by design per story spec (\"Do NOT add schema validation at write time\").\n- `import.meta.dirname` usage in tests — requires Node 20.11+, project targets Node 18. Established codebase pattern, not specific to this story.\n- Duplicate Ajv import and schema loading across two schema tests. Minor duplication.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None — all files above 80% floor, 96.79% overall.\n- Edge case: no test for concurrent writes to the same contract path (race condition between `.tmp` write and rename). Unlikely in sync code but possible with multiple processes.\n- No integration test verifying schema compatibility with the actual `OutputContract` TypeScript interface (schema tests only validate known-good/known-bad objects, not type-level alignment).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- `.tmp` file cleanup on `renameSync` failure: if `writeFileSync` succeeds but `renameSync` fails, the `.tmp` file is leaked. The AC explicitly allows this (\"the `.tmp` file may remain\"), so not fixed, but worth noting for future hardening.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed in this review session.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 8, Edit: 5, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1, Write: 0, other: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run` full suite (~30 lines each), `Grep writeStateAtomic` (~40 lines), `npm run build` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: one re-read of `output-contract.ts` returned cached result (acceptable — needed to verify final state after edits)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aaed40e65d57287f2 (use SendMessage with to: 'aaed40e65d57