{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q6y8PNz82wK8GZaNaf5tLx","type":"tool_result","content":"148\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 2)\n149\t\n150\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T02:00Z\n151\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T01:53 to ~2026-04-03T02:15 (approx. 22 minutes)\n152\t**Sprint progress:** 15/28 stories done (53.6%), Epics 1-4 complete, Epic 5 started\n153\t\n154\t---\n155\t\n156\t## 1. Session Summary\n157\t\n158\tThis session picked up story 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps at `review` status and drove it to `done`. No new stories were started.\n159\t\n160\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n161\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n162\t| 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps | code-review, verification, proof-doc fix, AGENTS.md update | **Done** | 14/14 ACs verified. Commit `b983273`. |\n163\t\n164\t**Activities completed:**\n165\t1. Code review found 2 HIGH bugs and 2 MEDIUM issues — all fixed\n166\t2. Test-provable verification: 14/14 ACs passed, 3963 tests green, 99.2% stmt coverage on workflow-engine.ts\n167\t3. Proof document formatting fix (needed `**Tier:**` bold format)\n168\t4. `src/lib/AGENTS.md` updated to include `source-isolation.ts` and `workflow-engine.ts`\n169\t\n170\t---\n171\t\n172\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n173\t\n174\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n175\t\n176\t| Severity | Issue |\n177\t|----------|-------|\n178\t| HIGH | Per-story RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK/SDK_INIT errors did not halt the outer flow loop — only the inner work-items loop. Catastrophic failures would be silently swallowed. |\n179\t| HIGH | Dispatch failures did not record a TaskCheckpoint in workflow state, violating AC #13. Crash recovery would lose track of failed tasks. |\n180\t| MEDIUM | Coverage gaps — 8 new tests added. Coverage improved to 99.2% stmt / 87% branch. |\n181\t\n182\t### LOW Issues Deferred (not fixed)\n183\t\n184\t- Duplicate checkpoint creation logic in `dispatchTask` else branch\n185\t- `handleDispatchError` and `recordErrorInState` could be merged\n186\t- `warn()` calls for skipped tasks don't propagate to `EngineResult.errors`\n187\t- Branch coverage at 87% — remaining uncovered branches are defensive null checks on YAML parse results\n188\t- No integration test verifying actual YAML parsing (all YAML mocked)\n189\t\n190\t### Infrastructure Issues\n191\t\n192\t- **AGENTS.md was stale** — missing entries for `source-isolation.ts` and `workflow-engine.ts`. Fixed in this session.\n193\t- **Prior action item resolved:** Action item #1 from Session 1 (\"Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1\") is now done.\n194\t- **Prior action item resolved:** Action item #3 from Session 1 (\"Update AGENTS.md\") is now partially addressed (2 of 5 missing modules added).\n195\t\n196\t---\n197\t\n198\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n199\t\n200\t### Subagent Token Report (this session only)\n201\t\n202\tFrom `.session-issues.md` token reports for the 5-1 phases that ran this session:\n203\t\n204\t| Subagent Phase | Tool Calls | Top Tools |\n205\t|---------------|------------|-----------|\n206\t| 5-1 code-review | 23 | Read: 10, Bash: 9, Edit: 5, Glob: 2, Skill: 1 |\n207\t| **Session Total** | **23** | Read: 10, Bash: 9, Edit: 5, Glob: 2, Skill: 1 |\n208\t\n209\tNote: The verification phase for 5-1 is not in the session issues log — it likely ran as part of the orchestrator or was not instrumented. The proof document and AGENTS.md update were additional orchestrator-level actions.\n210\t\n211\t### Observations\n212\t\n213\t- **Read-heavy session:** 10/23 tool calls (43%) were Read. Code review needs to read the implementation, tests, architecture, and existing code to find bugs.\n214\t- **Bash-heavy for code review:** 9 Bash calls — running tests after each fix. This is inherent to the fix-verify loop.\n215\t- **Redundant operations:** Coverage grep ran 3 times with different patterns (could be 1 call with combined pattern).\n216\t- **Largest Bash outputs:** Coverage run (~80 lines), vitest full suite (~10 lines), git diff --name-only (~11 lines).\n217\t- **Estimated session cost:** ~$3-4 (1 code-review phase + verification + minor fixups). This session was efficient — minimal waste.\n218\t\n219\t### Cumulative Cost Tracking\n220\t\n221\t| Session | Stories Completed | Estimated Cost | Cost/Story |\n222\t|---------|-------------------|---------------|------------|\n223\t| Prior sessions (Epics 1-2) | 7 | $37.08 | $4.45 |\n224\t| Session 1 (2026-04-03, early) | 2.5 | ~$12 | ~$4.80 |\n225\t| Session 2 (2026-04-03, late) | 0.5 (review+verify) | ~$3.50 | ~$7.00* |\n226\t\n227\t*Higher per-story cost for Session 2 is misleading — this was just the tail end (review+verify) of a story that was mostly built in Session 1.\n228\t\n229\t---\n230\t\n231\t## 4. What Went Well\n232\t\n233\t1. **Code review found 2 critical flow-control bugs.** The outer loop would have silently continued past catastrophic errors (RATE_LIMIT, NETWORK, SDK_INIT). This is exactly the kind of bug that only shows up in production.\n234\t2. **Clean verification:** 14/14 ACs passed on first attempt. No re-runs needed.\n235\t3. **AGENTS.md debt partially cleared.** Two missing module entries added.\n236\t4. **Focused session:** Single story, single goal, completed efficiently in ~22 minutes.\n237\t5. **Action items from Session 1 addressed:** The top priority action item (complete 5-1 review) is done.\n238\t\n239\t---\n240\t\n241\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n242\t\n243\t1. **AGENTS.md still has gaps.** Only `source-isolation.ts` and `workflow-engine.ts` were added. Still missing: `agent-dispatch.ts`, `agent-resolver.ts`, `session-manager.ts`, `trace-id.ts`.\n244\t2. **Verification phase not instrumented.** No token report for the 5-1 verification subagent — either it wasn't logged or ran inline. This is a gap in observability.\n245\t3. **`codeharness stats` still broken** for non-ralph sessions. No session-logs directory exists. Cost analysis relies entirely on manual extrapolation from subagent token reports.\n246\t4. **Coverage grep ran 3 times** during code review with different patterns — minor waste but symptomatic of the \"grep-and-check\" loop.\n247\t\n248\t---\n249\t\n250\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n251\t\n252\t### Patterns to Repeat\n253\t\n254\t- **Review-then-verify in a dedicated session works.** Separating the review/verify from the dev phase gave a clean, focused session with no context-switching.\n255\t- **Code review on flow-control logic is essential.** Error-handling paths in orchestrators are where the worst bugs hide. Both HIGH bugs were in error-handling branches.\n256\t\n257\t### Patterns to Avoid\n258\t\n259\t- **Multiple coverage grep patterns.** Use a single grep with OR pattern or just read the coverage summary file directly.\n260\t- **Leaving AGENTS.md updates incomplete.** If updating, update all missing entries in one pass — don't leave partial debt.\n261\t\n262\t---\n263\t\n264\t## 7. Action Items\n265\t\n266\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Status |\n267\t|---|--------|----------|-------|--------|\n268\t| 1 | ~~Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1~~ | ~~HIGH~~ | ~~Next session~~ | DONE |\n269\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness verify` to work without pre-set harness state flags | MEDIUM | Backlog | Open |\n270\t| 3 | Update `src/lib/AGENTS.md` — still missing: agent-dispatch, agent-resolver, session-manager, trace-id | MEDIUM | Next session | Partial |\n271\t| 4 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to work for non-ralph sessions | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n272\t| 5 | Sync `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` with `sprint-state.json` | LOW | Next session | Open |\n273\t| 6 | Fix pre-existing TS errors in `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n274\t| 7 | Address deferred LOW issues from 4-3, 4-4, and 5-1 code reviews | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n275\t| 8 | Add integration test for actual YAML parsing (not mocked) in workflow-engine | LOW | Backlog | New |\n276\t\n277\t---\n278\t\n279\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 3)\n280\t\n281\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T02:45Z\n282\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T02:12 to ~2026-04-03T02:39 (approx. 27 minutes)\n283\t**Sprint progress:** 17/28 stories done (60.7%), Epics 1-4 complete, Epic 5 at 2/4\n284\t\n285\t---\n286\t\n287\t## 1. Session Summary\n288\t\n289\tThis session completed one story end-to-end within a single ralph iteration (iteration #8).\n290\t\n291\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n292\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n293\t| 5-2-flow-execution-loop-blocks | create-story, dev-story, code-review, test-provable verification | **Done** | Full lifecycle in ~27 minutes. 10/10 ACs passed. Commit `1219d18`. |\n294\t\n295\t**Key deliverables:**\n296\t- `executeLoopBlock()` — loop block execution with termination on pass/maxIterations/circuit-breaker\n297\t- `parseVerdict()` — EvaluatorVerdict JSON parsing from dispatch output\n298\t- `buildRetryPrompt()` — finding injection into retry prompts\n299\t- `getFailedItems()` — failed-story-only retry filtering\n300\t- 27+ new tests, 3992 total tests passing, 96.37% statement coverage on workflow-engine.ts\n301\t\n302\t---\n303\t\n304\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n305\t\n306\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n307\t\n308\t| Severity | Issue | Impact |\n309\t|----------|-------|--------|\n310\t| HIGH | **Stale verdict bug** — verdict from a previous loop iteration could persist and cause premature loop termination on the next pass | Correctness: loop would exit early based on old evaluation results |\n311\t| HIGH | **80-line code duplication** — loop block dispatch logic duplicated the sequential step dispatch logic nearly verbatim | Maintainability: two copies of error handling, checkpoint logic, state updates that would diverge over time |\n312\t| HIGH | **Uncovered branches in duplicate code** — the duplicated code paths had no dedicated test coverage | Quality: bugs in the duplicate path would go undetected |\n313\t\n314\tAll three HIGH issues were fixed during code review before verification.\n315\t\n316\t### MEDIUM Issues (fixed)\n317\t\n318\tPer the parent session summary, 3 MEDIUM issues were also addressed during code review, likely related to coverage gaps and edge case handling.\n319\t\n320\t### Infrastructure Issues\n321\t\n322\t- **Session issues log stale** — `.session-issues.md` still contains only placeholder entries from 2026-03-18. The subagents this session did not write to it. The session issues log mechanism is non-functional for ralph-driven sessions.\n323\t- **`codeharness stats` still broken** — `stats --save` and `stats --json` both fail with \"No session-logs/ directory found.\" Cost analysis remains manual.\n324\t- **`ralph/.state-snapshot.json` divergence** — Shows `sprint.done: 12` but sprint-status.yaml shows 17 done. The state snapshot does not update Epic 5 stories as done (shows `storiesDone: 0` for Epic 5 despite 2 stories completed).\n325\t\n326\t---\n327\t\n328\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n329\t\n330\t### Session-Level Metrics\n331\t\n332\t| Metric | Value |\n333\t|--------|-------|\n334\t| Ralph iteration | #8 (of the current ralph run) |\n335\t| Log file size | 2.42 MB (`claude_output_2026-04-03_02-12-22.log`) |\n336\t| Session wall time | ~27 minutes |\n337\t| Phases completed | 4 (create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification) |\n338\t\n339\t### Estimated Token Usage\n340\t\n341\tBased on log file size (2.42 MB of stream-json output) and prior session correlations:\n342\t- Estimated API calls: ~15-25 (4 phases, each 4-7 tool calls)\n343\t- Estimated session cost: **~$4-5** (single story, full lifecycle)\n344\t- Cost per phase (estimated): create-story ~$0.50, dev-story ~$1.50, code-review ~$1.50, verification ~$0.75\n345\t\n346\t### Subagent Analysis (from parent session live log)\n347\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_012ujm5wbMMjNiJVhymSV3Q8","session_id":"be33ba5d-0e81-49c4-ae53-e69ac56cd1fb","uuid":"308e8aa7-6c82-43e5-b373-8860066d193c","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:20:21.157Z"}
