{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016Bo55bvYxM8n7uZvU2ifbc","type":"tool_result","content":"3328\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 10, Iteration 10, ~13:35–14:00)\n3329\t\n3330\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T14:00 UTC+4\n3331\t**Session window:** ~13:35 to ~13:55 (approx. 20 minutes)\n3332\t**Sprint progress:** 37/47 stories done (78.7%), Epics 1-11 complete, Epic 12 at 3/3 — **Epic 12 complete**\n3333\t\n3334\t---\n3335\t\n3336\t## 1. Session Summary\n3337\t\n3338\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n3339\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n3340\t| 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verify | **Done** | Full lifecycle. 9/9 ACs passed. Commit `69583ca`. Completes Epic 12. |\n3341\t\n3342\t**Net output:** 1 story completed and verified. Epic 12 (Multi-Framework Drivers) is now fully done — all 3 stories (12-1, 12-2, 12-3) shipped in back-to-back sessions.\n3343\t\n3344\t---\n3345\t\n3346\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n3347\t\n3348\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed in-session)\n3349\t\n3350\t| Severity | Phase | Issue | Fix Applied |\n3351\t|----------|-------|-------|-------------|\n3352\t| HIGH | code-review | Timer leak — `setTimeout` never cleared on success path in `checkDriverHealth()` | Added `clearTimeout` on resolution |\n3353\t| MEDIUM | code-review | Timeout error inaccuracy — reported ALL drivers instead of only non-responding ones (AC #6 violation) | Fixed to filter to only timed-out drivers |\n3354\t| MEDIUM | code-review | Double mock invocation — test called `checkDriverHealth` twice per assertion | Removed duplicate call |\n3355\t| MEDIUM | code-review | Missing test for \"timeout error reports only drivers that did not respond\" | Added new test case |\n3356\t\n3357\tCode review caught 1 HIGH and 3 MEDIUM issues. The HIGH timer leak would have caused resource exhaustion in long-running workflows. Good catch.\n3358\t\n3359\t### Technical Debt Introduced\n3360\t\n3361\t| Issue | Severity | Notes |\n3362\t|-------|----------|-------|\n3363\t| `HealthResult` type defined inline in function body | LOW | Cosmetic — code-review flagged but did not fix. Should be at module scope. |\n3364\t| `timeoutMs` optional parameter added for testability | LOW | Clean workaround for fake timer issues, but not in original spec |\n3365\t\n3366\t### Documentation Debt\n3367\t\n3368\t| Issue | Sessions Open | Notes |\n3369\t|-------|--------------|-------|\n3370\t| Stale AGENTS.md | **15th session** | Fixed this session — created `src/lib/agents/drivers/AGENTS.md`, updated `src/lib/AGENTS.md` and `src/lib/agents/AGENTS.md` |\n3371\t| Pre-existing lint error `require-yield` at `workflow-engine.test.ts:154` | Unknown | Not from this story; not addressed |\n3372\t\n3373\t### Verification Issues\n3374\t\n3375\t| Issue | Impact |\n3376\t|-------|--------|\n3377\t| Proof format mismatch — verifier generated `### AC N:` but parser expects `## AC N:` | Verifier had to rewrite proof document manually. Wasted ~2-3 tool calls. |\n3378\t| Stale AGENTS.md precondition failure | Fixed in verify phase itself — verify subagent updated AGENTS.md files |\n3379\t\n3380\t### Infrastructure Issues\n3381\t\n3382\t- **`codeharness stats --save` still broken.** No session-logs directory. Action #45 remains open.\n3383\t- **Multiple epics files with conflicting 12-3 definitions.** create-story had to determine correct source (epics-multi-framework.md). Risk of wrong story spec if sources diverge further.\n3384\t\n3385\t---\n3386\t\n3387\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n3388\t\n3389\t### Session-Level Cost\n3390\t\n3391\tNo per-session cost available (`codeharness stats` broken — action #45). Analysis based on subagent token reports from the session issues log.\n3392\t\n3393\t### Subagent Tool Call Breakdown (Story 12-3 only)\n3394\t\n3395\t| Phase | Tool Calls | Bash | Read | Edit | Write | Grep | Glob | Skill | Unique Files | Redundancy |\n3396\t|-------|-----------|------|------|------|-------|------|------|-------|-------------|------------|\n3397\t| create-story | 21 | 2 | 8 | 0 | 1 | 7 | 3 | 1 | 10 | None |\n3398\t| dev-story | 19 | 8 | 7 | 7 | 1 | 2 | 1 | 0 | 6 | workflow-engine.test.ts read 4x, workflow-engine.ts read 3x. One redundant `npm run build` |\n3399\t| code-review | 21 | 10 | 6 | 4 | 0 | 2 | 1 | 1 | 8 | None |\n3400\t| verify | 14 | 9 | 2 | 0 | 1 | 3 | 0 | 0 | 3 | npm run test:unit run twice (verbose + summary) |\n3401\t| **Total** | **75** | **29** | **23** | **11** | **3** | **14** | **5** | **2** | — | — |\n3402\t\n3403\t### Where Tokens Were Spent\n3404\t\n3405\t- **dev-story repeated reads:** `workflow-engine.test.ts` read 4 times, `workflow-engine.ts` read 3 times. This story modifies the workflow engine itself (not just a standalone driver), so the subagent needed multiple passes as it integrated the health check. Partially unavoidable, but a pre-loaded context strategy could cut 2-3 reads.\n3406\t- **code-review Bash-heavy (10 calls):** Ran builds, test suites, and coverage multiple times to verify each fix. This is expected when fixing 4 issues in-session.\n3407\t- **verify ran test suite twice:** Once with verbose output, once for summary. Could be combined into a single run.\n3408\t- **create-story Grep-heavy (7 calls):** Searched across multiple epic files to resolve the conflicting 12-3 definitions. This is a direct consequence of having multiple epics files.\n3409\t\n3410\t### Comparison: 12-2 vs 12-3\n3411\t\n3412\t| Metric | 12-2 (OpenCode) | 12-3 (Health Check) | Delta |\n3413\t|--------|-----------------|---------------------|-------|\n3414\t| Total tool calls | 59 | 75 | +27% |\n3415\t| Code-review fixes | 0 | 4 | +4 |\n3416\t| Redundant operations | 0 | 3 (reads + test run) | +3 |\n3417\t| Time (approx) | 18 min | 20 min | +11% |\n3418\t\n3419\t12-3 was more expensive because it touched the workflow engine (a central module) rather than adding an isolated driver file. The code-review phase found real bugs (timer leak, AC violation), so the extra cost was justified.\n3420\t\n3421\t### Cumulative Sprint Cost (from cost-report.md)\n3422\t\n3423\t| Metric | Value |\n3424\t|--------|-------|\n3425\t| Total API-equivalent cost | $202.85 |\n3426\t| Total API calls | 1,568 |\n3427\t| Stories completed | 49 (including orchestrator overhead) |\n3428\t| Average cost per story | $3.46 |\n3429\t| Most expensive phase | verify (44.3%, $89.96) |\n3430\t| Largest unattributed cost | \"unknown\" bucket ($33.23, 16.4%) |\n3431\t\n3432\t### Wasted Spend (this session)\n3433\t\n3434\t| Category | Estimated Waste | Notes |\n3435\t|----------|----------------|-------|\n3436\t| Redundant reads of workflow-engine files | ~$0.40 | 4x read of test file, 3x of source |\n3437\t| Duplicate test suite run in verify | ~$0.25 | Verbose + summary could be one run |\n3438\t| Redundant `npm run build` in dev-story | ~$0.15 | Build was already passing |\n3439\t| Proof format mismatch rewrite | ~$0.20 | Verifier had to redo proof document |\n3440\t| **Total** | **~$1.00** | Slightly higher than 12-2's $0.80 |\n3441\t\n3442\t### Cost Optimization Opportunities\n3443\t\n3444\t1. **Verify phase remains the #1 cost target (44.3%).** The proof format mismatch issue is a process bug — the verify template should document the expected format to avoid rework.\n3445\t2. **Pre-load central module context for integration stories.** Stories touching workflow-engine.ts should have it pre-loaded in the dev-story context, not discovered incrementally.\n3446\t3. **Combine test runs.** \"Run tests verbose\" + \"run tests summary\" should be a single `--reporter=verbose` call.\n3447\t4. **Resolve epic file conflicts.** Multiple epics files with different 12-3 definitions caused 7 Grep calls in create-story. Consolidate or add a manifest that points to the canonical source.\n3448\t\n3449\t---\n3450\t\n3451\t## 4. What Went Well\n3452\t\n3453\t1. **Epic 12 complete.** All three driver stories (12-1 codex, 12-2 opencode, 12-3 health check) shipped in consecutive sessions. The multi-framework driver foundation is done.\n3454\t2. **Code review caught a real resource leak.** The `setTimeout` timer leak in `checkDriverHealth()` would have caused issues in production workflows with many drivers. Review continues to earn its keep.\n3455\t3. **AGENTS.md finally fixed.** The verify subagent created `src/lib/agents/drivers/AGENTS.md` and updated parent AGENTS.md files. This was the longest-running open action item (15 sessions).\n3456\t4. **9/9 ACs passed on first verify.** Despite the proof format mismatch requiring a rewrite, all acceptance criteria passed without re-verification.\n3457\t5. **Timeout testability solved cleanly.** The optional `timeoutMs` parameter is a standard testing pattern — no hacks, no monkey-patching.\n3458\t6. **4,488 tests pass across 167 files, zero regressions.** Coverage stable at 96.79%.\n3459\t\n3460\t---\n3461\t\n3462\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n3463\t\n3464\t1. **Proof format mismatch in verify.** The verifier generated `### AC N:` headers but the parser expected `## AC N:`. This required a full rewrite of the proof document — wasted 2-3 tool calls and reasoning time. This is a tooling/prompt bug.\n3465\t2. **dev-story read workflow-engine files repeatedly.** 7 reads of 2 files. The health check integration required understanding the existing workflow engine flow, which the subagent built up incrementally rather than reading once.\n3466\t3. **`codeharness stats` still broken (15th session).** No session-logs directory. This forces manual cost estimation from subagent token reports every session.\n3467\t4. **classifyError/NETWORK_CODES duplication not extracted.** Action #41 is now in its 3rd session. Three drivers have identical implementations.\n3468\t5. **Multiple epics files caused confusion.** create-story spent 7 Grep calls resolving which file had the correct 12-3 definition.\n3469\t\n3470\t---\n3471\t\n3472\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n3473\t\n3474\t### Patterns to Repeat\n3475\t\n3476\t- **Code review before merge for integration stories.** 12-3 touched a central module (workflow-engine.ts) and code-review found a timer leak and an AC violation. For stories that modify shared infrastructure, code review is especially high-value.\n3477\t- **Fix documentation debt during verify.** The verify subagent fixed AGENTS.md — a 15-session-old action item — as part of its precondition checks. Let verify phases own documentation fixups when they encounter stale docs.\n3478\t- **Optional timeout parameters for testability.** Clean, standard pattern. Use it for any time-dependent code.\n3479\t\n3480\t### Patterns to Avoid\n3481\t\n3482\t- **Incremental discovery of central module context.** When a story integrates with workflow-engine.ts, the dev-story prompt should pre-load both the source and test file instead of letting the subagent read them piecemeal across 7 calls.\n3483\t- **Inconsistent proof format templates.** The verify phase needs a canonical proof format documented in its prompt. The `###` vs `##` mismatch is a recurring friction point.\n3484\t- **Deferring shared utility extraction indefinitely.** classifyError duplication has been flagged for 3 sessions. If it's not extracted before Epic 13, it will be 4+ drivers deep.\n3485\t\n3486\t---\n3487\t\n3488\t## 7. Action Items\n3489\t\n3490\t### Carried Forward (Status Update)\n3491\t\n3492\t| # | Action | Priority | Status |\n3493\t|---|--------|----------|--------|\n3494\t| 3 | Fix AGENTS.md for all new modules | HIGH | **CLOSED** — fixed in 12-3 verify phase |\n3495\t| 37 | Fix epic numbering mismatch | MEDIUM | Open |\n3496\t| 41 | Extract `classifyError` + `NETWORK_CODES` to shared driver utility | HIGH | Open — 3 sessions, 3 drivers duplicated |\n3497\t| 42 | Validate Codex CLI NDJSON output against real CLI | MEDIUM | Backlog |\n3498\t| 45 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` — no session-logs directory | LOW | Open — 15th session |\n3499\t| 46 | Remove dead fixture files in `test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/` | LOW | Open |\n3500\t| 47 | Standardize on inline test data for driver tests | LOW | Open |\n3501\t\n3502\t### New This Session\n3503\t\n3504\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n3505\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n3506\t| 48 | Fix verify proof format template — `## AC N:` not `### AC N:` | MEDIUM | Tooling |\n3507\t| 49 | Pre-load central module context for integration stories (workflow-engine.ts, etc.) | LOW | Process |\n3508\t| 50 | Consolidate epic files or add canonical source manifest | MEDIUM | Process |\n3509\t| 51 | Move `HealthResult` type to module scope in `checkDriverHealth` | LOW | Cleanup |\n3510\t| 52 | Investigate pre-existing `require-yield` lint error at `workflow-engine.test.ts:154` | LOW | Cleanup |\n3511\t\n3512\t### Priority Recommendations for Next Session\n3513\t\n3514\t1. **Extract shared driver utilities (action #41)** — 3 drivers with identical `classifyError` + `NETWORK_CODES`. Do this before Epic 13.\n3515\t2. **Epic 13 (output contracts)** — next epic. Stories 13-1, 13-2, 13-3.\n3516\t3. **Fix verify proof format (action #48)** — saves ~$0.20 per verify phase and eliminates a recurring friction point.\n3517\t4. **Fix epic file confusion (action #50)** — prevents wasted Grep calls in create-story.\n3518\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_012ujm5wbMMjNiJVhymSV3Q8","session_id":"be33ba5d-0e81-49c4-ae53-e69ac56cd1fb","uuid":"d396a71e-bfd3-46db-8ee9-ded78c4bbf7a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:20:37.916Z"}
