y subagent that ran this session. These are the raw materials for your retrospective — do not ignore them.\n\nCRITICAL: Run `codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nCRITICAL: The session issues log contains `## Token Report` sections from each subagent. Aggregate these to understand WHERE tokens were spent inside subagents (not just the parent). Look for:\n- Which subagent phases had the most tool calls?\n- Which subagents read the same files repeatedly?\n- Which Bash commands produced the largest outputs?\n- What redundant operations were reported?\nInclude this subagent-level breakdown in the cost analysis section.\n\nThis session completed 2 stories:\n1. **12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start** — was already implemented and verified from a previous session, but status was stuck at `backlog` due to sprint-state.json not being updated. Fixed status sync and marked done.\n2. **13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization** — full lifecycle: create → dev → review → verify → done. All 10 ACs passed. Code review found 2 HIGH (path traversal, empty input validation) and 3 MEDIUM issues, all fixed.\n\nAlso marked Epic 12 as done (all 3 stories complete).\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — which stories were attempted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize and analyze all issues from the session log\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report\n4. **What went well** — stories completed, bugs fixed, process improvements\n5. **What went wrong** — failures, blockers, stuck stories, wasted iterations\n6. **Lessons learned** — patterns to repeat or avoid\n7. **Action items** — concrete next steps\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-04-03.md. If a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"a3cad8ee4172bada5","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-04-03.md` (appended as Session 11, ~13:35-14:20).\n\n**Summary of what was produced:**\n\n- **Session summary:** 2 stories handled — 12-3 (status sync fix only) and 13-1 (full lifecycle, 10/10 ACs). Epic 12 closed.\n- **Issues analysis:** 2 HIGH bugs (path traversal, empty input validation), 3 MEDIUM issues — all fixed. Sprint-state.json sync bug continues to recur. Late-stage lint violations flagged as process gap.\n- **Cost analysis:** 67 subagent tool calls for 13-1, estimated ~$5 session cost, ~$208 cumulative. Lowest redundancy session (1 wasted operation vs 2-4 in prior sessions). Standalone modules are cheaper than integration stories.\n- **Key findings:** Code review caught 2 security bugs. Sprint-state.json sync is a persistent systemic issue (reported since Session 3). `codeharness stats` broken for 16th session.\n- **4 new action items** added (#53-56), 7 carried forward."}],"totalDurationMs":149354,"totalTokens":46446,"totalToolUseCount":22,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3762,"cache_read_input_tokens":42377,"output_tokens":306,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3762},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
